<subSubSection id="C3722A9E53693040BC3933900DE4F7BA" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD7791553693040BC3933900DE4F7BA" blockId="2.[297,1693,1343,2157]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">
A medium-sized, uniformly reddish yellow species, near 
<taxonomicName id="4C68029653693040B80533900D01F7ED" authority="Motschulsky" authorityName="Motschulsky" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scopaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testaceus">
<emphasis id="B91CA50753693040B80533900992F7D1" box="[1366,1693,2014,2054]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Scopaeus testaceus</emphasis>
Motschulsky
</taxonomicName>
, easily separated from it however, by the much wider and shorter, posteriorly broader head.
</paragraph>
